6. Create an `app.js` file in the project directory:
```javascript
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

app.get('/', (req, res) => {
  res.send('Hello World!');
});

module.exports = app;
```

7. Create a `cypress` directory in the project directory and initialize Cypress in it:
```bash
mkdir cypress
cd cypress
npx cypress open --config baseUrl=http://localhost:3000
```
This will open the Cypress test runner, where you can write your tests.

8. Inside the `cypress` directory, create a new test file, for example, `myFirstTest.spec.js`:
